717745f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 131st Street
717745f-a.text:
Manhattan College, Broadway at the N.E. corner of 131st Street,
showing also the north side of 131st Street from Broadway to Old
Broadway. The college has abandoned this building and moved to
the northernmost part of the Bronx; the present building will soon
be torn down, and the lot will be vacant as late as 1936.
April, 1926.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

721973f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 131st Street (West)
721973f-a.text:
60-66 Old Broadway, at, adjoining, and south of the S.W. corner
of West 131st Street. Nos. 64 and 66 are both frame houses.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 334.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.

717744f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 131st Street (West)
717744f-a.text:
Broadway, east side, north from W. 131st Street, showing
at the N.E. corner of that point, a cleared area and upon which
formerly stood Manhattan College. Tbthe north of same is the
Dash Co. garage and sales room occupying the balance of this
block front to 133rd Street. Note that W. 132nd Street is not
cut thru this block.
View No. 2 is a south eastward view across the aforerentioned
feature. Cn the right margin of this view aopears the steel
pillars of the elevated section of the I.R.T. subwav line.
April 1, 1938.
Views 1 a nd 2
P.L. Sperr

715551f-a.title: Manhattan: 131st Street (West) - Broadway
715551f-a.text:
622 West 131st Street, south side, between Broadway and
Twelfth avenue. This is a three-story frame house. The first
story has a brick front and the two upper stories are of wood.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 314
